<br>
To some extent, I understand why.  The Guides and GMs have enough to do dealing with real issues.  They don't have the time to police behavior.  They have to handle things like people with lost corpses, people with questions, people who think a quest is broken because...  You get the idea.<br>
<br>
Our best chance is to come up with a system that virtually everyone will agree to.  I can still have hopes.<br>
